Package de.oth.blocklib.world.structures

Author:
Chris Ebbinger (WS 2017/2018)
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Building
    Contains functions for creating buildings used in procedural structure generation.
    DoorWall
    A simple wall with a hole to be used as entrance to a room.
    Floor
    A solid horizontal wall used on the bottom of rooms.
    FullWall
    A simple, solid standing wall without any extras.
    Roof
    A wall type used to cover the top of a room.
    Room
    Contains data and functions for creating rooms used in structure generation.
    Structure
    Provides static functions for generating data needed to integrate structures into the world generation.
    StructurePopulator  
    Wall
    Provides functions for a single wall.
    WallFactory
    Provides a factory method for different wall types.
    WindowedWall
    A standing wall with windows.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Structure.Rotation
    Provides fixed rotation angles used to rotate structures counter-clockwise.
